{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:29:25.203Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Component Definition**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing a unified, premium layout system. I'm focusing on defining a `PremiumDataTable` component (or a module of these). This will replace existing table and filter elements in various pages, resulting in incredibly interactive and aesthetically pleasing interfaces. I'm planning to organize these new components inside `components/private-app/data-tables`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:29:26.997Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Component Architecture**\n\nI'm now wrestling with the architecture of these new components. Specifically, should I build a single, comprehensive `PremiumDataTable` that handles everything – filtering, table, drawer, and all – or should I build separate, composable components that work in harmony? The goal is to build a unified system. I'm leaning toward creating composable `PremiumFilterSystem` and `DetailDrawer` components alongside an enhanced `DataTable`, though I like the simplicity of a single component.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T03:29:29.158Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Component API**\n\nI've decided to provide *both* approaches! A powerful, highly-customized `PremiumDataTable` is the best solution for complex usage, and I've outlined its properties. It will accept data, columns, search fields, status/type filter options, status/type/date fields, a detail renderer (or a default key-value viewer!), empty state props, and a mobile card renderer. This component should cover *all* requirements! The search functionality will be a real-time search bar.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
